article.headline: Brown 86, Columbia 75
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Keenan Jeppesen matched his career high with 25 points, while Damon Huffman scored a career best 23, as Brown snapped a four-game losing streak with an 86-75 win over Columbia on Saturday night. John Baumann led Columbia with 19 points and Dragutin Kravic added 16. Baumann knocked down a jump shot that pulled Columbia (8-13, 1-7 Ivy League) within 54-52 midway through the second half. But Brown (7-14, 3-5) broke the game open with an 18-4 run. Huffman and Jeppesen each scored four points during the run and Nathan Eads, who finished with a career-high 12 points, capped it by converting a three-point play that gave Brown a 72-56 lead with 5:14 left. Columbia got no closer than 80-72 after a 3-point shot by K.J. Matsui with 1:20 remaining. The Bears were 30-of-43 from the line, while the Lions, who were called for 35 fouls, hit 13-of-23 foul shots. Columbia shot 59 percent in the first half to take a 43-39 halftime lead.
